<div id="review_3354625430" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3354625430" />
    <a title="Sofia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/114413220-sofia"><img alt="Sofia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607792875p2/114413220.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3354625430?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sofia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sofia" href="/user/show/114413220-sofia">Sofia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Someone who wants to feel pain</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Sofia by: </span>
      My own insane self
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=stock-side-characters">stock-side-characters</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=love-geometry">love-geometry</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=disappointments">disappointments</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=strong-female-protagonist">strong-female-protagonist</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=failed-romance">failed-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=well-that-was-a-cheap-plot">well-that-was-a-cheap-plot</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=epic-fantasy">epic-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=enough-with-the-rebellion">enough-with-the-rebellion</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=your-typical-ya-fantasy">your-typical-ya-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/114413220-sofia?shelf=my-villain-origin-story">my-villain-origin-story</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3354625430" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14124185547075158450">Alina and Mal are even bigger idiots in this one. I didn&apos;t know that was possible, but here we are.<br/><br/><br/>Somehow, Bardugo managed to squeeze every single YA trope into this book.<br/><br/>1. &quot;Please don&apos;t hurt him! I&apos;ll do anything!&quot;<br/>2. Love dodecahedron <br/>3. &quot;Plain&quot; MC with mousy brown hair *shudders*<br/>4. Bland love interest<br/>5. Stereotypical and predictable villain<br/>6. Idiotic MCs<br/>7. Comic relief<br/><br/>This book follows Alina and Mal, who are on the run from the Darkling. Alina has the first amplifier now, and is looking for </span>
  <span id="freeText14124185547075158450" style="display:none">Alina and Mal are even bigger idiots in this one. I didn't know that was possible, but here we are.<br /><br /><br />Somehow, Bardugo managed to squeeze every single YA trope into this book.<br /><br />1. "Please don't hurt him! I'll do anything!"<br />2. Love dodecahedron <br />3. "Plain" MC with mousy brown hair *shudders*<br />4. Bland love interest<br />5. Stereotypical and predictable villain<br />6. Idiotic MCs<br />7. Comic relief<br /><br />This book follows Alina and Mal, who are on the run from the Darkling. Alina has the first amplifier now, and is looking for the second. But the Darkling is on their <s>very obvious</s> trail, hoping to take over all of Ravka. <br /><br />Ahem. If you're running from a villain, don't pay for everything with your obviously expensive and unique hair pins. And don't stay in an inn. And don't flirt with the locals. <br /><br />And don't pick a buddy who will bail on you at the last second. I'm talking about Mal, of course. The whiny toddler. <br /><br />All he's supposed to do is track. And yet he gets all worked up because Alina is special now, and he doesn't want her to be special because that would mean "she doesn't love me anymore." Excuse me, she's trying to lead an army. Your petty jealousy is not helping anyone.<br /> <br />I just asked for some character development. Apparently that's too much for Moody Mal.<br /><br /><blockquote>
  <i>"Might want to leave him alone. That type needs plenty of time for brooding and self-recrimination. Otherwise they get cranky."</i>
</blockquote><br /><br />That's Mal for you.<br /><br />Throughout the book, he's called a "gifted tracker," but... he doesn't do any real tracking? He was supposed to be finding the sea whip, but how exactly did he do that? Even a talented tracker can't just trace an ancient, magical creature no one's ever seen through an entire sea. In a week.<br /><br />Everyone loves Nikolai, but honestly, the other characters are so bad that he seems amazing in comparison. I think he's actually a pretty average character, just in comparison, he's near perfect. <br /><br />I can't believe this is the same person who wrote King of Scars.<br /><br /><br />1 star</span>
  <a data-text-id="14124185547075158450" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

