        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2469889320" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13760695839419669682">Can we all just acknowledge the adorableness of David?? He and Nikolai deserve all the stars and to be honest their characters were the saving grace of this book. <br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1543863911ra/26682496.gif' width='400' height='250' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Alina was very frustrating at times. And I feel like I connected more with Mal to be honest. <br/><br/>Yes. THAT&apos;S RIGHT. I actually like Mal now?!?! Trust me, I didn&apos;t think I would. But I now understand his fears for Alina and his need to prove himself. <br/><br/>I enjoyed meeting new characters like Tamar and Tolya and Nikolai obviously. But some new c</span>
  <span id="freeText13760695839419669682" style="display:none">Can we all just acknowledge the adorableness of David?? He and Nikolai deserve all the stars and to be honest their characters were the saving grace of this book. <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1543863911ra/26682496.gif" width="400" height="250" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Alina was very frustrating at times. And I feel like I connected more with Mal to be honest. <br><br>Yes. THAT'S RIGHT. I actually like Mal now?!?! Trust me, I didn't think I would. But I now understand his fears for Alina and his need to prove himself. <br><br>I enjoyed meeting new characters like Tamar and Tolya and Nikolai obviously. But some new characters (*cough* Vasily *cough*) made me so mad. <br><br>Mal and Alina's relationship in this book left me face palming and had me rolling my eyes like crazy. I wanted to shout at both of them. <br><br>As much as I love Nikolai, not for one moment did I ship him with Alina. They just don't fit. <br><br>I get why many fans ship the Darkling and Alina. But I can't get over the things he's done. <br><br>All in all <i>Siege and Storm</i> was a bit slow. There were parts I loved and others that had me gritting my teeth and hoping something is going to happen. <br><br>I really hope things pick up in <i>Ruin and Rising.</i><br>_______<br><b>My reviews for</b> { all books in the Grishaverse} :<br><i>[Grisha Trilogy]</i><br>Book 1: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2469888928" rel="nofollow noopener">Shadow and Bone</a><br>Book 3: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2469889580" rel="nofollow noopener">Ruin and Rising</a><br><br><i>[Six of Crows Duology]</i><br>Book 1: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2598099625" rel="nofollow noopener">Six of Crows</a><br>Book 2: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2606611069" rel="nofollow noopener">Crooked Kingdom</a><br><br><i>[Nikolai Series]</i><br><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2535902543" rel="nofollow noopener">King of Scars</a><br><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2535902272" rel="nofollow noopener">Untitled book 2</a><br></span>
  <a data-text-id="13760695839419669682" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


